{
  "v": "2.0",
  "header": {
    "v": "0.2",
    "name": "MahTank Model.1946",
    "gameVersion": "0.2.50.10",
    "mass": 29832,
    "creationDate": "1944.06.05",
    "class": "",
    "desc": "In late 1944 after multiple problems with the model 1943 the army leadership finally dropped their facination for secondary turrets. An order for a single tank focused on catching up to foreign designs was commissioned. To speed up development the model 1944 hull was selected for refit. A more modern anti-tank gun was intended, though that project went into numerous issues which prompted the selection of the outdated 90mm as a stopgap. This gun was then fitted on a new modern turret. The final design was a step in the right direction but overall worse performing in most metrics relative to foreign designs.",
    "cost": 28797
  },
